        content: "Pick up your own iPhone or iPad. Open the gray Settings app, which looks like a gear icon. Tap your name at the very top of the Settings list. Tap \"Family\" or \"Family Sharing\" if you have not set it up yet, then tap \"Set Up Your Family.\" Follow the prompts to become the family organizer. Once family sharing is on, tap \"Add Member\" then \"Create Account for a Child.\" Apple will ask for the child's name, date of birth, and an email address Apple creates for them ending in icloud.com. Pick a strong password. Apple will charge a one-time small fee to your credit card to verify the parental consent step, often $0.50, which is then refunded. The child Apple ID now exists and is linked to your family, with you in charge.",
        warning: "Apple does not let you change a child's date of birth later. Enter the correct birthday the first time, because the wrong date can lock the child out of age-appropriate apps."
